We recommended that the Local Chief Executive ensure that:
The LGU will strictly comply with the documentary requirements as provided in DSWD Memorandum Circular No. 4, Series of 2020;
The necessary fund utilization and liquidation reports will be prepared and posted thereafter in the official website of the LGU as required by Section 87 of the General Appropriations Act of 2020 on the Implementation of Nationally Funded Projects;
Management will strictly ensure that only those with complete and appropriate supporting documents be allowed with actual disbursement, otherwise unreleased Emergency Subsidy Program (ESP) assistance should be returned and reported as refund, and;
Management will implement strict, proper monitoring and evaluation in the distribution of Emergency Subsidy Program (ESP) assistance through social amelioration measures, or any financial aid and assistance related to COVID-19 funds and ensure that such are under existing guidelines and pertinent laws and regulations.

We recommend that Management:
a. submit the lacking/deficient documents;
b. explain the reason for the delay/unfinished FMR Project;
c. constitute a functional technical working group that will ensure the proper
compliance of the project;
d. submit the Actual Cash Flow Program to guarantee that there is enough
funding to finish the contract;
This is without prejudice to any disallowance that may be issued if the
justification will not warrant.
Future projects for PAMANA should be properly planned and timelines
effectively followed, unless justified. Effective monitoring of the project is very
important in ensuring its proper implementation.
